subtasks.notes:
Isso será útil para podermos enviar o evento quando voltar a conexão.

"keen.created_at is a timestamp when the data reaches the Keen IO servers. It's set by Keen IO and cannot be overwritten.
keen.timestamp is the time the event actually occurred. The client can set this value to whatever time it wants. If no value for keen.timestamp is provided, it's also set to the time that Keen IO receives the data. 

Overwriting keen.timestamp is useful for applications that batch and send historical data, or aren't online all the time (example: mobile apps). "

https://groups.google.com/forum/#!searchin/keen-io-devs/created_at/keen-io-devs/BQ9rQfHExtk/lvk5LOeutygJ
